      "title": "GitHub suddenly rejected my SSH key (the fix was a .pub file?!)",
      "url": "https://thorsell.io/2026/07/21/github-ssh-keys.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/twqtlo",
      "score": 60,
      "comments": 18,
      "author": "GLaDER",
      "published": "2026-07-21T10:11:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "OpenSSH relies on local .pub files to determine public key metadata and negotiate modern SHA-2 signature algorithms with GitHub.",
        "Missing .pub companion files force OpenSSH to fallback to deprecated SHA-1 (ssh-rsa), causing GitHub to silently reject SSH connections.",
        "Ensure .pub files exist alongside private keys or migrate to ed25519 keys to prevent unexpected SSH authentication failures."
      ]
    },
